display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}=(a_{i,j})]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> be a real [or complex] number. We define the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Scalar Multiple</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> to be the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r\mathbf {A} = (ra_{i,j})]]></fr:tex> whose components are obtained by multiplying every component of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex>. We can also write this as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r\cdot  \mathbf {A}=r\mathbf {A}]]></fr:tex> to make the scalar multiplication explicit.</fr:p>
 
   
